title: AM
description: I really liked the instrumentation of this album, but I wasn't really able to connect with the lyricism.

title: 52nd Street
description: Great jazzy instrumentation, however it's a bit weaker than The Stranger in terms of lyricism.

title: The Stranger
description: An incredible album, each song has a different feel and a relatable message.

title: Desperado
description: I like the unique concept of the album, and it has some amazing songs on it. A lot of the filler songs don't have much replay value in my opinion.

title: Eagles
description: Really great first album that showcases the band's great vocal harmonies, I don't like the all the bird noises in Earlybird.

title: Jackson Browne
description: A really solid first album with most of the songs being great, however it feels a bit all over the place with the differing genres.

title: Late for the Sky
description: A brilliant album with no skips, great song-writing, and deeply personal songs.

title: American Teen
description: The hits on this album are great, but the rest of the songs are only okay and aren't too memorable.

title: Animals
description: I really like all of the instrumentation, especially in Dogs. The only thing holding this album back in my opinion is the talk box in Pigs.

title: On the Border
description: This album has very good highs, but also contains a lot of filler that differs in genre, which makes it feel disconnected.

title: The Long Run
description: This album has a few good hits, but the rest of the songs just aren't that good at all.

title: Meddle
description: I enjoy most of the instrumentation of this album, however I can't stand the dog noises in Seamus, this is the main reason for the lower score.

title: Christmas
description: This album has really great vocals and song selection, the only things holding it back in my review is that I can only listen to it 1 month out of the year and it only consists of covers.

title: Hands All Over
description: Aside from 1 or 2 hit songs, this album is very generic and the filler songs are not memorable.

title: x
description: Aside from Thinking Out Loud, the rest of this album has only okay songs with a few flagrantly bad ones.

title: Hozier
description: This album has a very nice theme and writing, the songs themselves aren't too memorable though.

title: 24K Magic
description: I liked most of the songs off this album, although it still is weaker than his previous two.

title: Thriller
description: This album has incredibly iconic songs and I liked them all. The other songs off this album that didn't become as popular are good but not great.

title: The Division Bell
description: This album has a few excellent songs, overall though it feels very long without need.

title: Born and Raised
description: This album is really well produced and has a great theme. My only quip is that the song lengths are drastically different.

title: An Evening with Silk Sonic
description: This album has a few nice hits, but the rest of it is only alright.

title: The Dark Side of the Moon
description: Really great instrumentation, really great lyrics, really great themes. Not much more can be said.

title: Axis: Bold as Love
description: Absolutely excellent electric guitar work, there were a few songs that had some weird effects but besides that this is a great album.

title: Electric Ladyland
description: Another amazing album from an instrumental standpoint. I think the writing has overall improved from Axis, however there are still weird effects I don't 100% like.

title: For Everyman
description: Overall very excellent album, my only gripe is that it isn't as profound of an album as Late for the Sky.

title: The Pretender
description: A few really good songs, the rest however are only okay with some weird experimentation.

title: Running on Empty
description: Very catchy album with great songs, although I'm really not fond of the song Cocaine, it feels completely disconnected from the rest of the album.

title: (What's The Story) Morning Glory?
description: This album has really great hits, the rest of the filler is decent but not great.

title: One of These Nights
description: Really catchy album, really great instrumentation. I wish the latter half of the album was more upbeat.

title: Hold Out
description: This album has some fine songs, I think it leans into the 80s vibe quite heavily, however I much prefer Browne's 70s sounding music.

title: Lawyers in Love
description: This album is very similar to Hold Out except a lot of the songs on this one have the same guitar intro, which I don't like.

title: Lives in the Balance
description: This album is better than I remember, I think the Latin influence works quite well with the theme of this album. It's hard to ignore the clunky parts of this album.

title: Minecraft - Volume Alpha
description: This album is very nostalgic to me and I recognized every song on it from when I was a kid. One issue I have with this soundtrack is that all of the songs sound very similar to each other and all follow a similar structure.

title: A Rush of Blood to the Head
To the Limit: The Essential Collection
